enchant
-------------------------------------------
The project aims to provide an efficient extensible abstraction for
dealing with different spell checking libraries.

Enchant is meant to provide a generic interface into various existing
spell checking libaries. These include, but are not limited to:
	* Aspell/Pspell
	* Ispell
	* Hspell
	* Uspell

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.18-1
  glib2-runtime-2.6.6-1
  libaspell15-0.50.3-1
  zlib-1.2.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.18-1
  autoconf2.5-2.59-3
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20050610-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  hspell-0.9-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.20-1
  make-3.80-1
  pkgconfig-0.17.2-2
  sed-4.1.4-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.abisource.com/enchant/

Canonical download:
  http://www.abisource.com/downloads/enchant/

----------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack enchant-1.2.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  ./enchant-1.2.0-X.sh all

This will create:
  /usr/src/enchant-1.2.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/enchant-1.2.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

